    <briefdescription>
<para>Documentation for compile-time configuration macros. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>The <computeroutput>DOXYGEN_DOCS</computeroutput> macro is used exclusively by documentation generators like Doxygen. Because minipaxtar enables reading and writing by default, these option macros (such as <computeroutput>MPTAR_NO_READ</computeroutput>) are not normally defined in the source code. Wrapping them in <computeroutput>&quot;#ifdef DOXYGEN_DOCS&quot;</computeroutput> allows Doxygen to index and document them without altering actual build configurations.</para>
<para>Stable configuration macros and custom conversion/string hooks.</para>
<para>These options, features, and custom conversion hooks are guaranteed stable and will follow standard deprecation cycles if ever slated for modification or removal. </para>
    </detaileddescription>
